\newlabel{eq:stage-routing}{{2}{2}{Problem Setting and RouteRec Overview}{equation.3.2}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Overall RouteRec framework. (a) RouteRec keeps the SASRec backbone and replaces shared feed-forward computation with stage-wise mixture-of-experts routing; stage features determine routing weights, while expert FFNs transform hidden states. (b) The routing computation is built from three reusable components: group-level routing, conditional within-group expert routing, and direct expert routing. (c) The three stages combine these components differently: the macro stage uses hierarchical routing, the mid stage blends hierarchical and direct routing, and the micro stage uses direct expert routing.}}{3}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:framework}{{2}{3}{Overall RouteRec framework. (a) RouteRec keeps the SASRec backbone and replaces shared feed-forward computation with stage-wise mixture-of-experts routing; stage features determine routing weights, while expert FFNs transform hidden states. (b) The routing computation is built from three reusable components: group-level routing, conditional within-group expert routing, and direct expert routing. (c) The three stages combine these components differently: the macro stage uses hierarchical routing, the mid stage blends hierarchical and direct routing, and the micro stage uses direct expert routing}{figure.caption.9}{}}
